ded to be, a powerfull damage dealer with great ac to take such damage. But we asked the wrong way, to be upgraded. The problem isn't warriors, its other classes becoming such a warrior almost to the point where warriors shouldn't even be a class anymore. Anyway, late for work and I know this will be flamed in a mtter of minutes so I'lll just say it....&quot;ON WITH THE NERFING!....NEXT IS JOO SK! /point <p>Boriis Substump
52 Dwarf Meatloaf
Says in dragon, "Fjtyjgf....ti gtetg rgf, frgf trytjj!"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucyrz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cyrz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 9:37:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Makes sense</span><hr size=1> I'm sure this thread will be deleted, but I have to speak up. I don't feel the need to cry &quot;On with the nerfs!&quot;. Nor do I feel the need to nerf SK's anymore.<br>
<br>
<br>
My main beef with the SK class was that they could hold aggro better at the expense of mana efficancy on heals. Combine this with the old ModRod2, making mana efficancy on heals meaningless. Now, mana efficancy is an object again. SK will still hold aggro better then us, and we will still be more mana efficent to heal with the changes.<br>
<br>
Ok, I still don't like SK's getting castable EB (Forget if it's Terror of Terris or Voice of Terris ATM), but it's not near as bad now that SK's weakness (Less mana efficancy on heals) is an actual weakness. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 456<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 9:55:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Nerfing doesn't always make sense.</span><hr size=1> Nerfing in general is bad.  It pisses people off.  Changes the game for them, usually in very negative ways, and generally breeds disatisfaction.<br>
<br>
However, there is a time and a place for it.  Particularly if a series of decisions has caused the game to go in a direction that was unintended and undesired.   Hopefully any further nerfs will be well thought out and deeply considered before implementation.  Detracting from people's playing experience without very compelling reasons is a good way to lose customers. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uslantedvision.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SlantedVision</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.slantedvision.com/break1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 10:14:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.slantedvision.com/break1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nerfing doesn't always make sense.</span><hr size=1> Well, while we haven't generally been given the best of the bonuses, however, while there are moments of nerfing, there are moments where classes are given a new toy or a new ability, these generally come with new expansions but compare your character to when the original Everquest came out, no longer are we drooling over short swords of the Ykesha, no longer are we hailing Ice Comet as the most powerful dmg spell.<br>
<br>
Over time, the game has shifted from melee to caster focus with most changes being done to the caster classes.   Clerics now have melee hammers that proc like crazy.<br>
<br>
All I'm saying is, don't let the days of nerfing cloud the days of enhancing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaveenlucenthawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aveen Lucenthawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 10:33:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nerfing doesn't always make sense.</span><hr size=1> This road has many bends along the forrested path, I don't think we have seen all that will come to pass.<br>
<br>
The changes they just made were very needed, and in light of them I think we are going to see a few more yet and perhaps some utility to the warrior class. So hang on, this is going to be a wild few weeks. <p>Aveen Lucenthawk<BR>
Myrmidon of 59 Battles<BR>
<a href=http://www.llts.org>LLTS!</a><BR>
Tarew Marr<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udumeshuhlbelk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dumesh UhlBelk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 250<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 11:02:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/w/i/wilsonua/DumStare.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nerfing doesn't always make sense.</span><hr size=1> Guys.... I hate to break it to you, but SKs taunt for @#%$ now.  They are barely above us in that category since the last few patches.  All their old fantastic taunt spells are nerfed to oblivion, and the results from the terror spells have been quite underwhelming.  SKs definitely do not need any nerf-bat attention. <p><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5309"target="_blank"alt = "Korak's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 10,10,900><b>Korak Sarathai - Barbarian Warlord - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12530"target="_blank"alt = "Dumesh's Megalo Profile"><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR = 900,10,10><b>Dumesh Uhl'Belk - Retired Troll Reaver - The Hand</b></FONT><BR></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhyardgune.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyardgune</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 11:34:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nerfing doesn't always make sense.</span><hr size=1> There is definitely no reason to start pointing fingers and asking for nerfs.  We may still fall way behind the knights in terms of xp group desirability, but these changes will go a long way toward giving us the MT role again.<br>
<br>
VI screwed up, they admitted it, and they are working to fix that.  That they admitted it so publicly and explained their reasons is at least admirable.<br>
<br>
Don't ask for nerfs because what goes around, comes around.  Don't gloat when someone else gets whacked by the nerf bat.  VI is making changes, be prepared for some pain, but be patient, I think in the end everyone will see benefits. <p>Hyardgune Varangian <BR> 58 Ogre Myrmidon of Gathered Might <BR> Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uxenojones.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 378<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/02 2:44:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Nerfing doesn't always make sense.</span><hr size=1> VI is &quot;apologizing&quot; because it is what sounds best, but I do not trust the spin they are putting on this nerf. <br>
<br>
First of all they say the mod-rod2 nerf is for the good of the mages and it will allow them to nuke more. WRONG! Since mages can not stack rods they will be constantly summoning rods in combat to feed the clerics and perhaps wizards and druids. If they really wanted to help mages on raids they would give them pets that would inspire confidence with the mage's guildmates. Most encounters my guild won't even let the mage with pet control summon one until the battle has started. Anyway this change has nothing to do with VI trying to make mages more enjoyable to play, but rather to make encounters harder for players. If they slow players down from reaching the end game the longer they feel we will play. I know alot of people stopped playing once they finished VT. VI doesn't want people to burn through Pop like some did with Luclin.<br>
<br>
<br>
Rollen <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showPrevMessage?topicID=1383.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showNextMessage?topicID=1383.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1383.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.emailToFriend?topicID=1383.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.threadControl?topicID=1383.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1383.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1383.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesteelwarriorthearena">The Arena<option value="thesteelwarriorthebattlefield">The BattleField<option value="thesteelwarriorthebunker">The Bunker<option value="thesteelwarriorthetavern">The Tavern<option value="thesteelwarriorfrm6">